2018/08/14
solution 1
1. Connect to MySQL from the MySQL command line client
1.1 start up mysql container
$ docker run --name some-mysql -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=my-secret-pw -d mysql:tag 
zhihu@zhihu:~/Desktop/docker/user_mgmt_project$ docker run --name mysql -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=root -d mysql:latest

1.2 connect to mysql command line
zhihu@zhihu:~/Desktop/docker/user_mgmt_project$ docker exec -it mysql sh -c 'exec mysql -h"localhost" -P"3306" -uroot -p'
Enter password: root

solution 2
From : https://hub.docker.com/_/mysql/
$ docker run -it --link some-mysql:mysql --rm mysql sh -c 'exec mysql -h"$MYSQL_PORT_3306_TCP_ADDR" -P"$MYSQL_PORT_3306_TCP_PORT" -uroot -p"$MYSQL_ENV_MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD"'

1.3 persistence dockered-mysql data --> mount a local volumn to mysql container data folder: /var/lib/mysql
docker run -it --name mysql -d -p 3306:3306 -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=root -v /home/zhihu/Desktop/docker/mysql/user_mgmt_project/data:/var/lib/mysql mysql:latest   

